  "body": "Before interacting with a network, `truffle` tests the state of a configured network using a `provider.testConnection` method defined [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/provider/index.js#L36-L73).\r\n\r\nFor the past week or so, `mainnet` along with other production test networks have been experiencing heavy congestion, causing the default timeout setting to throw.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, when upping the timeout to some high duration (`1e9` for example), `truffle` will hang and never resolve on the `getBlockByNumber` call occurring [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/provider/index.js#L58-L59).\r\n\r\n```\r\nâžœ  smoke-test truffle migrate --network rinkeby --skipDryRun\r\n\r\nCompiling your contracts...\r\n===========================\r\n> Everything is up to date, there is nothing to compile.\r\n\r\n```",
